HEADWORD: Chislev
<hw>Chis"lev</hw> <pr>(k⟦icr⟧s"l⟦ucr⟧f; k⟦icr⟧s"l⟦ucr⟧v;
k⟦emac⟧s*l⟦ecr⟧v")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.]</ety> <def>The third
month of the Jewish civil year; the ninth month of the ecclesiastical
year in the Jewish calendar, occupying a part of November and a part of
December; -- same as <er>Kislev</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Kislev.</syn>⟦br⟧
